reviewText: awesome , fast shipping and great price.

The DVD has three horror tales. I enjoyed "Hack" out of the three as it pays homage to slasher films...you know kids on an island getting hunted thing.

"Harm's Way" is about a woman at a safe house that is not so safe. Fairly boring "Lifetime" style film until the end twist.

"Baby Blues"  is a woman killing her kids. Seems to be done well, for what it was. I found it on the boring side.

If the price was cheap enough (no more than $2.00) and I hadn't seen any of the films, it would be a fair purchase.
These three films went above my expectations, usually these film sets are not to great but the films in this set were decent.
A com[lete waste of time and a perfectly good blank disc.
